No obvious sexual dimorphism in body ornamentation or skin tuberculation. The head and body of males and females of all sizes are covered with numerous unculiferous tubercles (
Fig. 4
). Adult males with slightly larger anal fins (up to 19.8 % SL vs. up to 15.5 % SL in females).

Distribution. This species is known from both the lower Malagarasi River and adjacent Luiche River (
Fig. 2
), and is typically found in small to moderate sized rapids.
